The Lagos State Government on Sunday ordered the temporary closure of Chrisland School, Opebi-Ikeja, following the reported death of a 12-year-old student of the school, Whitney Adeniran. Following the order, our correspondent, who was at the school on Monday, reports that security officials are at the entrance. ALSON READ: Chrisland schools break silence over death of female student Police vans, officers, and protesters are seen at the school premises. Relatives of the late students are also at the school entrance. Adeniran’s parents had on Saturday raised the alarm over the death of their daughter during the school’s inter-house sports event at Agege Stadium. 